## Transformation Algorithms

### Algorithm: Transforming Lucide Icons to Aucctus Icon Component
```
INPUTS: 
- Icon name from lucide-react (e.g., "Briefcase")
- Icon props (className, size, etc.)

STEPS:
1. Replace import statement:
   FROM: import { Briefcase } from 'lucide-react';
   TO:   import { Icon } from '@components';

2. Identify matching icon variant:
   - Use exact match when available (briefcase → briefcase)
   - Use closest match when exact isn't available:
     - ArrowDown → chevron-down
     - X → close
     - Check → check-circle
   - Refer to component mapping table for common mappings

3. Transform className:
   - text-primary → aucctus-stroke-primary
   - text-muted-foreground → aucctus-stroke-secondary
   - text-destructive → aucctus-stroke-error-primary

4. Set explicit dimensions:
   - h-4 w-4 → height={16} width={16}
   - h-5 w-5 → height={18} width={18}
   - h-6 w-6 → height={24} width={24}

5. Replace icon JSX:
   FROM: <Briefcase className="h-5 w-5 text-primary" />
   TO:   <Icon variant="briefcase" className="aucctus-stroke-primary" height={18} width={18} />
```

### Algorithm: Transforming Tailwind Classes to Aucctus Theme Classes
```
INPUTS:
- Tailwind className string (e.g., "text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-4")

STEPS:
1. Identify and replace text color classes:
   - text-primary → aucctus-text-primary
   - text-muted-foreground → aucctus-text-secondary
   - text-destructive → aucctus-text-error-primary

2. Identify and replace background color classes:
   - bg-background → aucctus-bg-primary
   - bg-muted → aucctus-bg-secondary
   - bg-destructive → aucctus-bg-error-primary

3. Identify and replace border color classes:
   - border-primary → aucctus-border-primary
   - border-muted → aucctus-border-secondary
   - border-destructive → aucctus-border-error

4. Identify and replace typography classes:
   - text-xs → aucctus-text-xs
   - text-sm → aucctus-text-sm
   - text-base → aucctus-text-md
   - text-lg → aucctus-text-lg
   - text-xl → aucctus-text-xl
   - font-medium → aucctus-text-md-medium (or appropriate size)
   - font-semibold → aucctus-text-md-semibold (or appropriate size)
   - font-bold → aucctus-text-md-bold (or appropriate size)

5. Retain spacing, sizing, flex, and other utility classes:
   - mr-4, p-2, h-full, w-full, flex, gap-2, etc.

6. Replace hover classes:
   - hover:bg-accent → aucctus-bg-primary-hover
   - hover:text-accent-foreground → aucctus-text-secondary-hover

7. Structure final className value:
   - Group related classes together (aucctus theme classes first, then utilities)
   - Use consistent ordering (text, bg, border, size, spacing, flex, other)
```

### Algorithm: Converting State Management with Mock Data
```
INPUTS:
- External state implementation
- External state operations

STEPS:
1. Define mock data structure:
   - Ensure it has proper id fields (string, not number)
   - Include all necessary properties from external data
   - Add timestamps or other internal required properties

2. Initialize state with mock data:
   FROM: const [jobs, setJobs] = useState<Job[]>(initialJobs);
   TO:   const [mockJobs, setMockJobs] = useState<MockJob[]>(initialMockJobs);

3. Transform CRUD operations:
   - Create: Add id generation and timestamp creation
   - Read: Use useMemo for derived lists or filtered data
   - Update: Use id-based updates instead of index-based
   - Delete: Use id-based filtering instead of splice

4. Add appropriate toast notifications:
   - toast.success for successful operations
   - toast.error for error handling

5. Implement additional sorting or filtering with useMemo:
   const sortedJobs = useMemo(
     () => [...mockJobs].sort((a, b) => (a.order || 0) - (b.order || 0)),
     [mockJobs],
   );
```

## Decision Trees

### Decision Tree: Component Selection

```
IF external component is Card
  THEN use div with aucctus-bg-primary aucctus-border-secondary classes
  
ELSE IF external component is CardHeader
  THEN use SectionHeader component
  
ELSE IF external component is CardTitle
  THEN use title prop of SectionHeader
  
ELSE IF external component is CardContent
  THEN use div with px-4 py-2 classes
  
ELSE IF external component is Button
  IF variant is "ghost"
    THEN use button with aucctus-bg-secondary-hover class
  ELSE IF variant is "outline"
    THEN use button with btn btn-light class
  ELSE IF variant is "default"
    THEN use button with btn btn-primary class
  ELSE IF variant is "destructive"
    THEN use button with btn btn-danger class
  
ELSE IF external component is a Lucide icon
  THEN use Icon component with variant property and proper stroke class
  
ELSE IF external component is Input
  THEN use input with aucctus-bg-primary aucctus-border-secondary classes
  
ELSE IF external component is Label
  THEN use label with aucctus-text-primary aucctus-text-sm classes
  
ELSE IF external component is Select
  THEN use select with aucctus-bg-primary aucctus-border-secondary classes
  
ELSE IF external component is Checkbox
  THEN use input type="checkbox" with aucctus-border-secondary class
  
ELSE IF external component is Dialog
  THEN use custom modal implementation
```

### Decision Tree: Text Class Selection

```
IF external class contains text-primary
  THEN use aucctus-text-primary
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-secondary or text-muted-foreground
  THEN use aucctus-text-secondary
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-destructive or text-error
  THEN use aucctus-text-error-primary
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-success
  THEN use aucctus-text-success-primary
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-warning
  THEN use aucctus-text-warning-primary
  
IF external class contains text-xs
  THEN include aucctus-text-xs
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-sm
  THEN include aucctus-text-sm
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-base
  THEN include aucctus-text-md
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-lg
  THEN include aucctus-text-lg
  
ELSE IF external class contains text-xl
  THEN include aucctus-text-xl
  
IF external class contains font-medium
  THEN append -medium to the text size class
  
ELSE IF external class contains font-semibold
  THEN append -semibold to the text size class
  
ELSE IF external class contains font-bold
  THEN append -bold to the text size class
```

### Decision Tree: Background Class Selection

```
IF external class contains bg-background or bg-white
  THEN use aucctus-bg-primary
  
ELSE IF external class contains bg-muted or bg-gray-100
  THEN use aucctus-bg-secondary
  
ELSE IF external class contains bg-destructive or bg-red
  THEN use aucctus-bg-error-primary
  
ELSE IF external class contains bg-success or bg-green
  THEN use aucctus-bg-success-primary
  
ELSE IF external class contains bg-warning or bg-yellow
  THEN use aucctus-bg-warning-primary
  
IF external class contains hover:bg
  THEN replace with corresponding aucctus-bg-*-hover class
```

## Common Pitfalls

### 1. Class Name Transformation Errors
```
❌ INCORRECT: hover:aucctus-bg-primary
✅ CORRECT: aucctus-bg-primary-hover

❌ INCORRECT: text-muted-foreground
✅ CORRECT: aucctus-text-secondary

❌ INCORRECT: className="aucctus-bg-primary hover:aucctus-bg-primary-hover"
✅ CORRECT: className="aucctus-bg-primary-hover"
```

### 2. Icon Component Implementation
```
❌ INCORRECT: <Icon variant="briefcase" className="h-5 w-5 text-primary" />
✅ CORRECT: <Icon variant="briefcase" className="aucctus-stroke-primary" height={18} width={18} />

❌ INCORRECT: <Icon type="briefcase" />
✅ CORRECT: <Icon variant="briefcase" />
```

### 3. Button Component Styling
```
❌ INCORRECT: <button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700">Submit</button>
✅ CORRECT: <button className="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>

❌ INCORRECT: <button className="aucctus-text-primary aucctus-bg-primary">Cancel</button>
✅ CORRECT: <button className="btn btn-light">Cancel</button>
```

### 4. Missing or Incorrect ARIA Attributes
```
❌ INCORRECT: <button onClick={handleDelete}><Icon variant="trash" /></button>
✅ CORRECT: <button onClick={handleDelete} aria-label="Delete item"><Icon variant="trash" /></button>
```

### 5. State Management Approaches
```
❌ INCORRECT: Using index-based updates with mockJobs
✅ CORRECT: Using id-based updates with mockJobs

❌ INCORRECT: Modifying mockJobs directly
✅ CORRECT: Using setMockJobs with a new array
```

## Edge Cases

### Complex Form Elements
When porting form elements with validation:
```tsx
// EXTERNAL
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";
import { z } from "zod";
import { Form, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormControl, FormMessage } from "@/components/ui/form";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";

const formSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(2).max(50),
  email: z.string().email(),
});

function ProfileForm() {
  const form = useForm<z.infer<typeof formSchema>>({
    resolver: zodResolver(formSchema),
    defaultValues: {
      name: "",
      email: "",
    },
  });

  function onSubmit(values: z.infer<typeof formSchema>) {
    console.log(values);
  }

  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className="space-y-8">
        <FormField
          control={form.control}
          name="name"
          render={({ field }) => (
            <FormItem>
              <FormLabel>Name</FormLabel>
              <FormControl>
                <Input placeholder="Your name" {...field} />
              </FormControl>
              <FormMessage />
            </FormItem>
          )}
        />
        {/* More fields */}
        <Button type="submit">Submit</Button>
      </form>
    </Form>
  );
}

// INTERNAL
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { FormField } from '@components';

interface FormValues {
  name: string;
  email: string;
}

function ProfileForm() {
  const [formValues, setFormValues] = useState<FormValues>({
    name: '',
    email: '',
  });
  const [errors, setErrors] = useState<Partial<FormValues>>({});

  const validateForm = (): boolean => {
    const newErrors: Partial<FormValues> = {};
    
    if (!formValues.name || formValues.name.length < 2 || formValues.name.length > 50) {
      newErrors.name = 'Name must be between 2 and 50 characters';
    }
    
    if (!formValues.email || !/^\S+@\S+\.\S+$/.test(formValues.email)) {
      newErrors.email = 'Please enter a valid email address';
    }
    
    setErrors(newErrors);
    return Object.keys(newErrors).length === 0;
  };

  const handleChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    const { name, value } = e.target;
    setFormValues(prev => ({ ...prev, [name]: value }));
  };

  const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (validateForm()) {
      console.log(formValues);
    }
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="space-y-8">
      <FormField
        label="Name"
        name="name"
        error={errors.name}
      >
        <input
          className="aucctus-bg-primary aucctus-border-secondary aucctus-text-primary p-2 rounded-md border w-full"
          name="name"
          value={formValues.name}
          onChange={handleChange}
          placeholder="Your name"
        />
      </FormField>
      
      {/* More fields */}
      <button type="submit" className="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

